I"I<p>Haplotype phasing involves distinguishing the two parentally inherited copies of each chromosome into haplotypes. <a href="https://odelaneau.github.io/shapeit5/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SHAPEIT5</a> is a tool for statistical population-based haplotype phasing which focuses specifically at extremely rare variants.</p>

